The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Army meet

 New Delhi, Oct. 21 (PTI): The Indian Army will get its first-ever expert outsiders? view on the relevance of its tactics and doctrines when seven of its former chiefs meet here tomorrow for a three-day conclave.

 The former chiefs will dwell upon the army?s operational scene at the macro level and ponder over new tactics and doctrines. The star at the meet will be the hero of the 1971 Indo-Pak war, Field Marshal Sam Manekshaw. 

 Army chief General .C. Vij, who wants an ?outside view? on where the forces are headed and whether they are keeping pace with modern and future warfare, mooted the conclave. 




